A security guard sustained three gunshot wounds in an attack in Three Rivers in Vereeniging on Friday.The 34-year-old guard was found in a security vehicle.ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said: &#8220;The man sustained gunshot wounds to his shoulder, hip and the upper leg.&#8221;Paramedics assessed the guard before transporting to Mediclinic Vereeniging for further medical care.The South African Police Service (SAPS) are investigating the case as the circumstances surrounding the incident are not yet known.-TNA Reporter 